      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Critics will argue that free speech is not absolute and that regulation is necessary to prevent demonstrable harm, such as the spread of illegal content or incitement to violence. They will claim that the \"marketplace of ideas\" fails when misinformation or hate speech causes real-world damage. To counter this, you must argue that the *definition* of \"harm\" is being weaponized by the state to silence legitimate dissent, and that the cure—government censorship—is worse than the disease.",
      "source": "target",
