      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. It's basically saying that once you let the government decide what's \"harmful,\" the principle of free speech is essentially dead. Do you think most people and legal scholars would agree that any form of regulation is fundamentally a step toward censorship, or is that a pretty extreme way of looking at it?",
